description.narrative:
The Project's development impact will include:
i) Support the all-important tourism sector in an FCS and IDA country;
ii) Contribute to private sector development through the provision of scarce long-term financing to a local company that has long operating track record;
iii) Rehabilitate a popular trekking trail in a remote area which was badly affected by the 2014 Everest avalanche and 2015 earthquakes and blockade;
iv) Provide employment to local communities, especially given tourism is largely the only source of income for the local Sherpa community; 
v) Stimulate foreign exchange inflow and domestic government receipts;
vi) Develop and sustain village communities along the trail by supporting local SMEs; 
vii) Facilitate better medical and emergency preparedness in the Khumbu/Everest region, by stocking lodges with Emergency Medical Oxygen at all times to treat high altitude sickness, and by training locals in search and rescue operations in the Khumbu region;  
viii) Help increase the standards of service throughout the Everest region, and to contribute to increased revenue generation and economic growth in the Khumbu/Everest region. Better services provided by the lodges are expected to help raise the overall standards of hospitality in the region, and attract higher paying customers and better revenues to the hospitality sector in the region.
